quran[55]{c,v,t}:
  82,1,When heaven is split open
  82,2,when the stars are scattered
  82,3,when the seas swarm over
  82,4,when the tombs are overthrown
  82,5,"then a soul shall know its works, the former and the latter"
  82,6,O Man! What deceived thee as to thy generous Lord
  82,7,who created thee and shaped thee and wrought thee in symmetry
  82,8,and composed thee after what form He would
  82,9,No indeed; but you cry lies to the Doom
  82,10,yet there are over you watchers
  82,11,"noble, writers"
  82,12,who know whatever you do
  82,13,Surely the pious shall be in bliss
  82,14,and the libertines shall be in a fiery furnace
  82,15,roasting therein on the Day of Doom
  82,16,nor shall they ever be absent from it
  82,17,And what shall teach thee what is the Day of Doom
  82,18,"Again, what shall teach thee what is the Day of Doom"
  82,19,A day when no soul shall possess aught to succour another soul; that day the Command shall belong unto God
  83,1,Woe to the stinters who
  83,2,"when they measure against the people, take full measure"
  83,3,"but, when they measure for them or weigh for them, do skimp"
  83,4,Do those not think that they shall be raised up
  83,5,unto a mighty day
  83,6,a day when mankind shall stand before the Lord of all Being
  83,7,No indeed; the Book of the libertines is in Sijjin
  83,8,and what shall teach thee what is Sijjin
  83,9,A book inscribed
  83,10,Woe that day unto those who cry it lies
  83,11,who cry lies to the Day of Doom
  83,12,and none cries lies to it but every guilty aggressor
  83,13,"When our signs are recited to him, he says, 'Fairy-tales of the ancients"
  83,14,No indeed; but that they were earning has rusted upon their hearts
  83,15,No indeed; but upon that day they shall be veiled from their Lord
  83,16,then they shall roast in Hell
  83,17,"Then it shall be said to them, 'This is that you cried lies to"
  83,18,No indeed; the book of the pious is in Illiyun
  83,19,and what shall teach thee what is Illiyun
  83,20,A book inscribed
  83,21,witnessed by those brought nigh
  83,22,Surely the pious shall be in bliss
  83,23,upon couches gazing
  83,24,thou knowest in their faces the radiancy of bliss
  83,25,as they are given to drink of a wine sealed
  83,26,whose seal is musk -- so after that let the strivers strive
  83,27,and whose mixture is Tasnim
  83,28,a fountain at which do drink those brought nigh
  83,29,"Behold, the sinners were laughing at the believers"
  83,30,when them passed them by winking at one another
  83,31,and when they returned to their people they returned blithely
  83,32,"and when they saw them they said, 'Lo, these men are astray"
  83,33,Yet they were not sent as watchers over them
  83,34,So today the believers are laughing at the unbelievers
  83,35,upon couches gazing
  83,36,Have the unbelievers been rewarded what they were doing